page.title: 05Housing in Northern Baldock
page.content:
Square 9 of the block includes the northern part of Baldock, a market town of about 12 000 people. This is mainly a residential area.
Most of the housing is yellow brick Victorian terracing, built between the town centre and the railway station. Some 20th century housing has been built in this infill area, probably on old Victorian terrace sites.
Immediately South of the railway station are 1930's semis and 1970's 5 bedroom mock Georgian houses.
North of the station is a small area of private housing just completed. This, combined with development elsewhere in Baldock, is a good example of very recent urban expansion.
